                <p class="text-justify">Allegiant Airlines is an ultra-low-cost American airline founded in 1997 as WestJet Express. It is also the fourteenth-largest commercial airline in North America. The airline operates its services offers service to 129 destinations throughout the United States, mostly to smaller non-hub regional airports and all usually only a few times each week with a fleet size of 121 aircraft. </p>
                <p class="text-justify">If you have plans to book flight tickets from AllegiantAirlines, make sure you check the ongoing offers and deals to save on your traveling. Below is an overview of <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/allegiant-airlines-refund-policy.aspx">Allegiant Airlines’ refund policy</a> for your ease. </p>
                <h2>Refund policy </h2>
                <p class="text-justify">All types of refunds including the refund of fees for unused optional services due to oversells and <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/cancellation-policy.aspx">flight cancellations</a> are covered under Allegiant Airline’s <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/refund-policy.aspx">refund policy</a>. You will receive the refund in the same source you used for the purchase of the ticket. For instance, if you used debit card to purchase the ticket, the refund will be made to the same card within 7 days of the request date. If you paid for tickets via cash or check, you will receive the refund within 20 days of the receipt of complete documentation by Allegiant. </p>
                <p class="text-justify">If you have paid for the tickets in installments via third party, the refund request will be made to the airline but the settlement must be managed by the third party. </p>
                <h3>Frequently asked question</h3>
                <h3 class="text-justify">Who can receive a refund with Allegiant Airlines? </h3>
                <p class="text-justify">If you have purchased the ticket, you are eligible to receive a refund. You must provide necessary documents confirming that you have paid for the ticket such as an invoice or credit card. However, if the person who paid for the ticket couldn’t collect refund due to sickness or death, the refund will be issued to an immediate family member, subject to the person providing a death certificate or medical certificate. </p>
                <h3 class="text-justify">How to cancel a flight ticket with Allegiant Airlines? </h3>
                <p class="text-justify">If you wish to cancel the flight ticket, you may call the Allegiant Airlines customer care office and inform them about the cancellation. Also, you can visit the official website of the airlines and cancel your flight ticket. </p>
                <h3 class="text-justify">How can I make the request for a refund? By when can I expect it? </h3>
                <p class="text-justify">In order to make a request for a refund, you can visit the official website of Allegiant Airlines and fill out the refund request form. It may take 7 to 20 business days for the refund to reflect on your card/bank statement. </p>
                <h3 class="text-justify">Can I ask for compensation if my flight gets delayed by 2 hours? </h3>
                <p class="text-justify">There can be a possibility that your replacement flight delays your arrival by 2 or more hours or your flight was canceled less than 14 days before departure, you are eligible to get compensation. </p>
                <h3 class="text-justify">Is my flight refundable? </h3>
                <p class="text-justify">Though such information is mentioned on the ticket, you can check if your flight is refundable by visiting the official website of the airline and entering the ticket or document number. It will display refund eligibility and information. </p>

